        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 4:22PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Jackson Mill, or 11 miles northwest of Weston, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Weston, Jackson Mill, Camden, Avon, and Leopold.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
